AgentInvokeRequest.description:
Request model for agent invocation.

Attributes:
    input: The input message to send to the agent
    thread_id: Optional thread ID to continue a conversation
    enable_streaming: Whether to enable streaming responses
    show_tool_calls: Whether to show tool calls in the response
    output_schema: Optional schema for structuring the response
    json_schema: Optional JSON schema for validating the response
    enabled_tools: Optional list of tool IDs to enable for this invocation
    metadata_filter: Optional filtering of datasource resources by metadata.

        Supports both legacy and enhanced formats:

        1. Legacy format (simple list per datasource - implicit AND):
        {
            "datasource_id_1": [
                {"field": "metadata_variable_1", "values": ["allowed_value_1", "allowed_value_2"]},
                {"field": "metadata_variable_2", "values": ["allowed_value_3"]}
            ],
            "datasource_id_2": [
                {"field": "metadata_variable_3", "values": ["allowed_value_4", "allowed_value_5"]}
            ]
        }

        2. Enhanced format (MongoDB-style with $and/$or operators):
        {
            "datasource_id_1": {
                "$and": [
                    {"field": "category", "values": ["fruits"]},
                    {"$or": [
                        {"field": "price", "values": [1.0, 2.0]},
                        {"field": "rating", "values": [5]}
                    ]}
                ]
            },
            "datasource_id_2": {
                "$or": [
                    {"field": "type", "values": ["premium"]},
                    {"field": "discount", "values": [true]}
                ]
            }
        }

        The enhanced format allows for complex nested filtering with any combination
        of AND/OR logic while maintaining security through validated leaf conditions.
    documents: Optional list of URL-only document objects.
